Definition: a bond issued by a corporation
Example: carries no claim to ownership and pays no dividends but payments to bondholders have priority over payments to stockholders; a corporate bond is a safer investment than common stock in the same company
Synonyms: bond, a, issued, by, corporation, carries, no, claim, to, ownership, and, pays, dividends, but, payments, bondholders, have, priority, over, stockholders, corporate, is, safer, investment, than, common, stock, in, the, same, company
Category: noun.possession
